text: Schakowsky Commemorates Memorial Day
label: HH2

text: WASHINGTON, DC (May 31, 2010) – Rep. Jan Schakowsky (D-IL) delivered the following
label: BODY

text: remarks today at a ceremony to commemorate Memorial Day.  Schakowsky participated in the
label: BODY

text: Norwood Park Memorial Day Parade.
label: BODY

text: "Today, on Memorial Day, we pause to recognize those men and women who gave their lives in
label: BODY

text: defense of our country.  We should also redouble our commitment to caring for and serving our
label: BODY

text: veterans and military families who make enormous sacrifices to keep our nation safe and
label: BODY

text: secure.
label: BODY

text: "Last week, together with other members of the Congressional Caucus on Women’s Issues, I
label: BODY

text: laid a wreath at Arlington Cemetery to honor all servicewomen who gave their lives for their
label: BODY

text: country.  Like their male colleagues, they often leave behind families, young children, and loved
label: BODY

text: ones.  Today, we recognize and honor their sacrifice, and the sacrifice of their families.
label: BODY

text: "We must pay tribute to them both through our words and through our actions.  We have a
label: BODY

text: responsibility to provide for the men and women currently serving in our military, as well as to
label: BODY

text: ensure that our veterans receive the benefits and services they deserve.
label: BODY

text: Schakowsky Commemorates Memorial Day
label: HH2

text: "On Friday, the House passed the American Jobs and Closing Tax Loopholes Act.  This bill
label: BODY

text: begins to phase out the Disabled Veterans Tax, which unfairly forces disabled military retirees
label: BODY

text: to give up one dollar of their pension for every dollar they receive in disability pay.  Veterans
label: BODY

text: forced to retire early because of severe service-connected injuries deserve full disability and
label: BODY

text: retirement pay, and, under this legislation, they will finally be able to receive these benefits.
label: BODY

text: "We also passed the National Defense Authorization Act, legislation which will provide our
label: BODY

text: troops with the resources they need to defend the United States.  This bill provides a pay
label: BODY

text: increase for service members, contains critical benefits for the families of soldiers, strengthens
label: BODY

text: military readiness by providing essential equipment, and helps protect our troops both at home
label: BODY

text: and abroad.
label: BODY

text: "We are also working to provide the benefits that our veterans have earned.  President
label: BODY

text: Obama’s fiscal year 2011 budget includes $125 billion for the Department of Veterans Affairs for
label: BODY

text: fiscal year 2011.  This is an $11 billion increase over the previous year and will help the VA
label: BODY

text: modernize and better assist our veterans in meeting the challenges of today.
label: BODY

text: "The VA continues to face a rapidly expanding caseload, and resources have not kept pace with
label: BODY

text: that demand.  Over a million claims were received last year, and that number will continue to
label: BODY

text: climb.   I have heard countless heartbreaking stories of claims taking years to process, and I
label: BODY

text: know the devastating impact those delays can have on families, particularly in today’s economic
label: BODY

text: climate.
label: BODY

text: Schakowsky Commemorates Memorial Day
label: HH2

text: "My office continues to work with veterans to help them access their benefits, but this is a much
label: BODY

text: broader problem.  In order to meet this ever-growing demand, I strongly support President
label: BODY

text: Obama’s proposal to devote an additional $460 million to cutting the backlog.  This funding will
label: BODY

text: allow the VA to hire over 4000 additional claims processors.
label: BODY

text: "Last fall, we celebrated the opening of a new location for the Community Based Outpatient
label: BODY

text: Clinic (CBOC) in Evanston.  The new CBOC has the capacity to serve more veterans than ever
label: BODY

text: before, helping us provide quality care for our ever-growing veteran population.
label: BODY

text: "On a national level, on May 5th President Obama signed the Caregivers and Veterans
label: BODY

text: Omnibus Health Services Act of 2010 into law.  This legislation, which passed both Houses of
label: BODY

text: Congress unanimously, creates a support system for veteran caregivers that includes training,
label: BODY

text: education, and financial assistance.  This legislation also provided major improvements in
label: BODY

text: mental health services, health care services for America’s women veterans, services for
label: BODY

text: homeless veterans, and programs to assist rural veterans.
label: BODY

text: "We also continue to work to ensure that all eligible veterans can access the benefits of the
label: BODY

text: 2008 Post 9/11 GI bill, which expanded the promise of a full, four-year education to veterans of
label: BODY

text: the wars in Iraq and Afghanistan.  This landmark legislation authorized the largest educational
label: BODY

text: assistance program in over fifty years; now, we have to take further steps to ensure that the VA
label: BODY

text: is able to cope with those new demands.  To do that, Secretary Shinseki has proposed a plan to
label: BODY

text: automate the processing of applications for benefits under the Post 9/11 GI Bill.  This effort will
label: BODY

text: help bring the VA into the 21st century, allowing the agency to process an ever-growing number
label: BODY

text: of claims.
label: BODY

text: Schakowsky Commemorates Memorial Day
label: HH2

text: "President Obama’s FY 2011 budget also includes $4.2 billion to tackle homelessness among
label: BODY

text: our veterans.  The VA has estimated that at least 131,000 veterans are homeless on any given
label: BODY

text: night.  Though the agency already operates the largest system of assistance programs for the
label: BODY

text: homeless in the United States, too many veterans still do not know where they will sleep each
label: BODY

text: night.  The proposed increase will allow the VA to greatly expand its services for the homeless.
label: BODY

text: "I met last week with Labor Secretary Hilda Solis and she told us about a new joint effort
label: BODY

text: between her Department and the Department of Housing and Urban Development to address
label: BODY

text: the health, housing, and employment needs of homeless veterans- men and women and their
label: BODY

text: families.
label: BODY

text: "Further, President Obama’s budget includes $5.2 billion for mental health, which will fund the
label: BODY

text: diagnosis and treatment of depression, substance abuse, post-traumatic stress disorder, all of
label: BODY

text: which can be debilitating to veterans and their families.  A study published last year found that
label: BODY

text: nearly 40% of Iraq and Afghanistan veterans enrolled in the veterans health system had been
label: BODY

text: received mental health diagnoses.  Of these, 22% were for post-traumatic stress disorder, and
label: BODY

text: 17% were for depression.  As the number of veterans experiencing mental health difficulties
label: BODY

text: continues to rise, it is vital that we increase our efforts to help these men and women.
label: BODY

text: "As co-chair of the Congressional Women’s Caucus, I would particularly like to highlight the
label: BODY

text: progress we are making toward meeting the specific needs of female veterans.  There are
label: BODY

text: approximately 1.8 million female veterans in the United   States right now.  With more and more
label: BODY

text: women breaking down barriers and serving our country in the armed forces, we need to do
label: BODY

text: more to ensure that female veterans can access a full range of services and benefits.
label: BODY

text: Schakowsky Commemorates Memorial Day
label: HH2

text: "It has been estimated that the number of female veterans enrolled in VA medical care could
label: BODY

text: increase by another 30% in the next five years, so it is critical that we act quickly to ensure that
label: BODY

text: the VA is able to meet their needs.  The proposed FY 2011 budget includes $217.6 to meet
label: BODY

text: gender-specific health care needs of female veterans, money that will enable the VA to improve
label: BODY

text: the quality of care, as well as improvements in privacy and security.
label: BODY

text: "We’ve also started planning for the future.  In October, President Obama signed H.R. 1016, the
label: BODY

text: Veterans Health Care Budget Reform and Transparency Act, into law.  This landmark
label: BODY

text: legislation, which I strongly support, will guarantee timely and predictable funding for the VA by
label: BODY

text: allowing Congress to fund veterans’ health care a year in advance of the regular appropriations
label: BODY

text: process.  This will help to ensure that veterans’ medical care is not held up by political delays.
label: BODY

text: In keeping with this legislation, the administration has requested $54.3 billion in advance
label: BODY

text: appropriations for 2012 for health care.
label: BODY

text: "Finally, I want to highlight the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act, which funded critical
label: BODY

text: infrastructure improvements while also creating jobs for American workers.  In particular, this bill
label: BODY

text: funds many much-needed improvements for the Department of Veterans Affairs, including
label: BODY

text: hospital renovations, new troop and family housing, and facilities to help returning soldiers
label: BODY

text: transition to civilian life. The ARRA also helps fight unemployment among veterans by providing
label: BODY

text: a tax credit to businesses that hire recently discharged veterans.
label: BODY

text: "In Washington, we remain committed to supporting members of our armed forces and their
label: BODY

text: families, as well as providing our veterans with the benefits and services they have earned.  As
label: BODY

text: the wars in Iraq and Afghanistan stretch on, and more young men and women elect to serve
label: BODY

text: their nation overseas, it becomes increasingly critical to improve and expand the range of
label: BODY

text: benefits they receive when they return home."
label: BODY
